          <mj-text align="left" padding="0">
            <h2>
              Stencila Open: Reproducible research collaboration &amp; publication, minus the headaches.
            </h2>

            <p>
              Working towards realizing a future of easily shareable
              data-driven documents, we have had to lay a lot of groundwork
              in order to realize our goal.
            </p>

            <p>
              As we continue working towards our ultimate vision, we realize
              that many of you face daily challenges which we might already
              be able to help with.
            </p>

            <p>That is why we created Stencila Open, an online tool demonstrating the combined power of our work so far.</p>


            <p><strong><a href="https://hub.stenci.la/open/">Stencila Open</a> allows you to convert documents between multiple file formats, select a theme to suit your needs, and share your work with peersâ€”all the while preserving reproducibility.</strong></p>

            <p>
              You can quickly share your manuscripts as online web pages for feedback, send Jupyter/R Notebooks to less technical collaborators who prefer Microsoft Word, or to simply convert between file formats.
            </p>

            <p>
              There are a lot more teamwork opportunities enabled by Open, so we invite
              you to <a href="https://hub.stenci.la/open/">take it for a spin</a> and let us know what you think.
              Stencila Open is free to use, and as with all our work, is open-source.
            </p>
          </mj-text>

          <mj-button padding="24px 0" href="https://hub.stenci.la/open/"> Try Stencila
